items.text:
Hi everyone! I have an UNPAID casting and crew opportunity in Hatfield, Hertfordshire.

The production name is 'All That We Feared'.

I'm looking for a male actor for the main role of 'Arlo Jones'

Applicants must be 16+. Playing age of around 17-21. There are no physical requirements for this role.

I'm also seeking for:

-Someone to do sound, own equipment preferably but not required. 

-Lighting, please note this will take place outside with no access to plugs. For this crew role you'll need your own equipment.

-AC, with knowledge of the following; how to pull focus, swapping lenses and general handling.

This production will be taking place on the 2nd November, 3rd November and 1 more date in November that hasn't been decided yet but will likely take place on a weekend.

This project is unpaid. Travel and accommodation are sadly not able to be covered but food and drink will be provided of course. 

This project is perfect for people who are eager to get experience and be on set. To the people who may have an issue with these terms for filming, I completely understand but sadly they are non-negotiable.

To those interested please send me an email ASAP on rdawsonproductions@outlook.com

Hope you've all had/will have an amazing day, thank you!

items.text:
Important announcement 
 ‚Ä™@SMG4‚Ä¨ ‚Äã  ‚Ä™@GLITCH‚Ä¨ ‚Äã 
As I am still working on Cameron: Into The Multiverse, I've watched my hero "SMG4" Video saying he's going to be leaving soon on his channel. I want to take a moment to tell you all that he was more then my hero. He was my idol. I watched his videos when I was a kid. I grew up laughing, and crying of all his amazing videos over the years and now. Sadly. I guess the time has come. I'm gonna miss him. He really changed my life and gave me a dream to be like him someday and that I will become as I continue bringing you all joy, so please, comment in the chat "Farewell SMG4, Thank you for everything." In order to honor him as we continue our lives and as I give you all the upcoming film you deserve. 

Here's his YouTube channel link
https://youtube.com/@smg4?si=4OU0nd3utv-Np_RN

Thank you SMG4. 

Dear Smg4, I don't know if you or any other business associates would read this but. I'm so thankful for the inspiration, you given me over the years. I used to watch you when I was a kid. I always enjoyed your stories, your movies. Even the memes. Mostly you are the main reason why I started my own company. It's called XPA Studios Company. I been making animation for years and I've always tried so hard to be like you someday. It wasn't easy but I had help from my family. Mostly I never stop making movies and shows for the world cause. I know that someday. I would bring peace to the world because I knew it could bring me a purpose. So i understand you want to post the last video of your channel. I understand, but. I hope someday. We could work together. It's always been a dream to have XPA Studios Company working with Glitch Productions. Anyway. I gotta work on my film. So. Thank you. For everything and just to introduce myself.  My name is Cameron Croff and I'm from America in Warren, Ohio.
#Smg4 #Xpastudios4ever #supportanshare #follow #ANIMATEDMOVIE #animation #YouTube #Cartoon #2danimation #cartoonseries #fypanimations #viral

items.text:
** CASTING CALL ‚Äì VANCOUVER **

**We‚Äôre still looking to fill a few key roles for our upcoming short film shooting mid-November in Vancouver, BC.**

**Logline:**

After her brother kills the nanny who tormented them as children, a teenage girl must cover up the crime while fractured memories of their past resurface ‚Äî forcing her to choose between protecting him or saving herself.

**Production Details**

 Location: Vancouver, BC

 Shoot Dates: November 20,21,22 

 Genre: Psychological Drama / Thriller

 Non-Union / Volunteer

**ROLES WE‚ÄôRE CASTING**

**Sawyer (14‚Äì15 years old)**

Sensitive and unguarded, Sawyer is still haunted by the trauma of his childhood. Desperate to protect himself, he makes a choice that leads to violence and binds him to his sister‚Äôs protection.

**Katherine (30s)**

Outwardly polished and dependable, Katherine hides a cold, controlling nature. To the world, she‚Äôs a caretaker ‚Äî but to the children, she‚Äôs a source of lasting fear and trauma.

**TO SUBMIT:**

Please send your **headshot, r√©sum√©, and demo reel (if available)** to

**thethingsweburyshortfilm@gmail.com**

with the subject line:

[ROLE NAME] ‚Äì [Your Name]

Once we‚Äôve received your submission, we‚Äôll send audition sides and next steps.

We‚Äôre reposting this call in hopes of finding the right fits for these remaining roles ‚Äî please share with Vancouver actors who might be interested!

items.text:
Hey, I am the 1st AD for a VFS Student Final Film. 

We are currently looking for anyone interested in being a Background Actor. 

This is a Student Film, so this is volunteer work. But, we will have Crafty on location for you. 

Logline: An ambitious Art professor sabotaged his gifted student out of jealousy to finally pursue his lifelong dream.

Location: Downtown/Greater Vancouver Area 

We are looking for: 

4 Art Students - Aged 20-25 

You will be needed November 26th and 27th

~20 Art Patrons - Aged 25+ 

You will be needed November 28th 

Times will be given as soon as I have them, but assume you will be there from 9:00am to 8/9 PM, including a 1 hour lunch. 

Please email us if you are interested! 

Email: deathofanartistshort@gmail.com

(LIVE/In person open call auditions)

Date: Saturday 11/01/25 (November 1, 2025) and 11/2/25 (November 2, 2025

Time: 9am 

Location: K75 STUNT ACADEMY 13560 49th St N Suite 10, Clearwater, FL 33762

 

VUONA Entertainment is seeking experienced stunt performers for overseas contracts in China

‚Äã

Male 5‚Äô6‚Äù and above (170cm+) and Female 5‚Äô5‚Äù and above (165cm+) stunt performers of all ethnicities, ages 18+

Must be proficient in at least one of the following:

Fight choreography / screen combat

High falls

Fire burns

Wire work

Vehicle or motorcycle stunts

Acrobatics / parkour

Water or underwater stunts

Specialty skills (jet-ski, high divers, etc)

 

REQUIREMENTS:

1. Current stunt headshot, resume and demo reel (can be sent to k75stuntacademy@gmail.com, subject STUNT SHOW)

2. Must be physically fit, safety-conscious, and able to follow direction

3. Flexible and comfortable working in various weather and terrain conditions.

Day of Audition will consist of:

1. Pull ups

2. Cardio

3. Agility

4. Mat work: front and back, dive rolls, cartwheels, etc

5. Fight Choreography

6. Type-outs throughout audition 

Please bring printed headshot and resume to audition. 

Please bring your hydration, towel and running shoes 

No weapons allowed (prop or otherwise)

No work boots or sandals allowed 

No food allowed inside gym

Vuona at K75 Auditions form:

https://forms.gle/GibBXWPAu4xYfY198

Thank you 

#Stunts #Stunt #China #Choreography #Fire #Action

üé¨ CASTING NOW ‚Äì Male Lead for Short Period Drama

We‚Äôre urgently casting for Ed Morris, the lead role in The Stuntman ‚Äî a 3-minute period drama made as part of our final year at UWE Bristol.

The film will be shot in Bristol on 11th & 12th November 2025. This is a student production (unpaid, with travel expenses covered) and will be shown at our university showcase and submitted to film festivals.

Story: Set in 1920s Wiltshire, The Stuntman follows Ed Morris, a small-town silent cinema owner fighting to keep his theatre alive as the arrival of sound threatens to change film forever. Determined to save his livelihood, he stages one final ambitious stunt ‚Äî a warm yet bittersweet story about passion, creativity, and the struggle against inevitable change.

Role: Ed Morris (Lead, 28) Charming, intelligent, and hardworking. Outwardly confident, but quietly desperate as he clings to his dream of preserving silent cinema. Must have strong screen presence and emotional depth.

üé• Self-tape deadline: Thursday 30th October
üíª Zoom recalls: Friday 31st October
üìç Filming: 11th & 12th November (Bristol area)

To apply, please send your headshot, CV (or Spotlight/Mandy link), and self-tape to: Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

# Casting Call: German-Speaking Content Creators (Tech)

We‚Äôre a tech brand looking for fluent (native-level) German creators to film simple scripted UGC videos.

**What you‚Äôll do**
* Shoot 2‚Äì3 short videos following our provided script (total time on set: ~2‚Äì3 hours).
* Self-shoot at home or on location with clean light and clear audio.
* Deliver fast ‚Äî we move quickly.

**You have**
* Native or near-native German.
* Proven self-shooting experience (UGC, reels, ads, or similar).
* A good camera setup (modern smartphone or mirrorless), tripod, and basic audio.
* Reliable turnaround.

**Compensation**
* From **$150** (TBD based on scope and deliverables).

**What we provide**
* Script + shot list
* Creative notes and framing/safe-zone guidelines

**How to apply**

** ‚äπ ‡£™ **CASTING CALL**‚äπ ‡£™ Àñ**

We are casting for 'Muddy Waters'! 

Please read through the details & character descriptions and send us your audition, or share with people who might be interested!

UBC Student Thesis Short Film

Non-Union, Unpaid/Volunteer (crafty provided)

**Location**: Metro Vancouver

**Shoot Dates:** February 6-8th, 2026

**Logline:** Set in the 90s‚Äî Jeannie, an anomalous young adult, unearths an unexpected connection with a marsh creature when she and her friends cast a spell for revenge.

**Genre:** Fantasy, Drama with comedic/camp tones.

**Themes:** Identity, Gender Envy, Found Family, Belonging, Angst.

**Submission Instructions:**

Please submit a **SELF-TAPE** and/or **DEMO REEL** along with your **HEADSHOT** to [muddywatersfilm@gmail.com](mailto:muddywatersfilm@gmail.com).

Please include your **NAME, HEIGHT, LOCATION**, the** ROLE(s)** you are auditioning for, and confirm that you are **ABOVE THE AGE OF 18**. Acting Resume is optional.

Please submit by **NOVEMBER 3rd**.

*Self-Tape/Demo Reel submissions will still be accepted until December but talent may miss out on in-person audition/chemistry read opportunities if submitted at a later date.*

‚Äß‚ÇäÀö ‚èæ. ‚ãÖ

Please note that this is a queer film. Absolutely ZERO hate or discrimination will be tolerated. We will be casting self-identifying queer individuals for all of the queer characters. Even for non-queer characters, we will only be working with talent who are, at the very least, allies in agreement to make the production a safe space. We will also NOT be asking anyone to ‚Äúprove‚Äù their identities to us. What you choose to share with us regarding your gender identity and/or sexuality is entirely up to you. MON√ìLOGO MANIFESTO 
RESPEITEM MINHA PROFISS√ÉO 
EU ESTUDEI 

Eu estudei.
Sim, eu estudei.
Enquanto o mundo dizia ‚Äúarruma um emprego de verdade‚Äù,
eu estava dentro de uma sala preta,
decorando texto, suando ensaio,
vivendo de passagem de √¥nibus e sonho.

Eu n√£o ca√≠ do nada num palco, n√£o nasci com um filtro na cara.
Eu me formei no suor, no corpo, na l√°grima.
Eu aprendi que a arte √© sagrada,
e que pra subir num palco, primeiro √© preciso respeitar o ch√£o.

Mas agora‚Ä¶
agora eu vejo o palco sendo tomado por quem nunca pisou numa coxia.
Por quem nunca entendeu o que √© dividir um figurino rasgado,
ou comer um p√£o dormido depois do ensaio,
porque o cach√™ ainda n√£o saiu.

Enquanto eu estudo personagem,
tem influenciador interpretando ‚Äúartista‚Äù.
Enquanto eu busco o DRT,
tem gente ocupando vaga de quem vive da arte,
sem nem saber o peso dessa sigla:
Direito, Registro, Trabalho.

DRT n√£o √© papel. √â identidade.
√â o selo que diz: eu lutei, eu aprendi, eu sou profissional.

Mas parece que o pa√≠s esqueceu o que √© ser artista.
Esqueceu que existe uma lei.
Lei 6.533 de 78.
Quase cinquenta anos dizendo:
‚ÄúPra exercer profiss√£o art√≠stica, precisa registro.‚Äù
Mas ningu√©m cumpre.
Ningu√©m fiscaliza.
E a gente, que vive disso,
vira invis√≠vel no pr√≥prio palco da vida.

Eu n√£o quero mais aplauso de pena.
Eu quero contrato!
Eu quero cach√™ digno!
Eu quero respeito!

Porque a arte √© o meu trabalho.
E trabalho n√£o √© favor, √© direito.

Quantas vezes eu j√° ouvi:
‚ÄúFaz por amor.‚Äù
Eu fa√ßo por amor, sim.
Mas o amor n√£o paga aluguel.
O amor n√£o compra tinta pra cen√°rio.
O amor n√£o enche o prato dos meus filhos.

Chega.
Chega de achar que artista vive de vento.
Chega de ver prefeitura contratando quem n√£o tem registro,
produtora escalando influenciador no lugar de ator,
plataforma pagando mis√©ria e chamando de ‚Äúoportunidade‚Äù.

Eu sou artista registrado!
E ser registrado n√£o √© vaidade ‚Äî
√© resist√™ncia!

Cada carimbo na minha carteira √© uma cicatriz de luta.
Cada ensaio √© uma batalha travada contra o esquecimento.
Cada espet√°culo √© um ato pol√≠tico.

Porque quando eu subo no palco,
eu n√£o estou representando um personagem
eu estou representando uma classe inteira,
massacrada, subestimada, explorada.

Eu vi artistas passarem fome.
Vi t√©cnicos dormindo em teatro fechado.
Vi companhias inteiras desaparecerem na pandemia.
E mesmo assim, a gente volta.
Volta com a cara pintada, com o corpo ferido,
mas com a alma acesa.

Porque o artista de verdade nunca desiste.
Ele renasce a cada ensaio.
A cada aplauso.
A cada cena que salva uma vida.

Ent√£o escuta:
se voc√™ trabalha com arte,
registre-se.
Se voc√™ contrata arte,
respeite o DRT.
E se voc√™ consome arte,
entenda que por tr√°s de cada cena
existe um trabalhador.

#ArtistaRegistrado n√£o √© s√≥ uma hashtag.
√â um grito.
√â um pedido de socorro.
√â um manifesto de classe.

Porque sem artista registrado,
n√£o existe arte profissional.
E sem respeito,
n√£o existe cultura viva.

Eu sou artista.
Sou registrado.
Sou resist√™ncia.
E ningu√©m vai me tirar do meu palco.

Halloüëãüèª Wir suchen f√ºr unser neues No- Budget- Serien- Projekt noch EINE hobbym√§√üige SCHAUSPIELERIN (w/d) f√ºr unser neues Projekt! Es wird sp√§ter noch ein Buch zur Staffel geben.

Titel: Siegerlandchaos Staffel 2: Traumawut + Abschlussepisode: Untergangseuphorie 

Genre: Krimi mit Fantasy- Elementen, Drama 

Logline:
Der Fokus liegt auf Lea, welche lernen muss, mit ihrem Trauma umzugehen, und dabei sowohl eine zerst√∂rerische als auch vers√∂hnliche Seite an sich entdeckt. Au√üerdem stellen sich die Fragen, was in Zukunft aus Sherlock Wickels Detektei werden soll und wer ein echtes oder ein falsches Spiel spielt. 

Zusammenfassung
Ausgangspunkt: Bei einem tragischen Ereignis verliert Lea ihre Ehefrau Maja, sowie so ziemlich alles, was ihr etwas bedeutet. Es stellen sich die Fragen, ob Maja noch lebt oder nicht, und wo der Verantwortliche f√ºr das Drama steckt. Lea gelangt langsam aber sicher an ihr Limit, w√§hrend Sherlock Wickel sie im Stich zu lassen scheint. 

Konflikt: Es gibt mehrere Konflikte. Eine Psychiatrie sollte Ben Saalfeld heilen, aber verdarb ihn, Aufgrund der Umst√§nde. Rache m√∂chte er an Sherlock Wickel, Markus Wattson und insbesondere Lea nehmen. Hilfe bekommt er dabei von Sarahs Erzfeind Ludwig, beruhend auf Gegenseitigkeit. Ludwig m√∂chte mit Jacks Kette, Sarah und Maja einen moralisch zwiesp√§ltigen Plan umsetzen, um sich selbst von Auswirkungen seiner Schuld zu befreien. Gleichzeitig geht es innerhalb seiner Organisation ebenfalls nicht mit rechten Dingen zu. 

Aufl√∂sung: Am Ende erh√§lt Lea wichtige Erkenntnisse √ºber 's sich selbst Verzeihen. Die Organisation wird √ºberf√ºhrt und die Detektei geschlossen. Es gibt Vers√∂hnungen, Happy Ends und Drama. Maja, Emmas bzw. Jillians Eltern, Ludwig, Liora und Ben werden sterben. Sherlock Wickel und Lea lernen, das Gl√ºck in kleinen Momenten zu sehen. 

Stimmung: Intensiv, d√ºster, humorvoll, spannend, mysteri√∂s, actiongeladen, nah an realen Erfahrungen mit Traumata 

Besonders geeignet f√ºr Menschen, die sich tiefer mit Gef√ºhlen auseinandersetzen m√∂chten. 

Das Drehbuch enth√§lt 125 Seiten, wovon bereits 11 gedreht wurden. Gedreht wird vermutlich wie gewohnt in Plittershagen (Freudenberg, NRW, nahe Siegen) und einem noch unbekannten Drehort als Leas zu Hause. Es sind ggf. Hunde vor Ort, weshalb Tierliebhaber erw√ºnscht sind :) Fahrtkosten k√∂nnen leider nicht √ºbernommen werden, aber f√ºr Spa√ü, Speis und Trank ist nat√ºrlich gesorgtüòä

Ziel des Projekts: Wir m√∂chten mit einer packenden Geschichte die Leute dazu bewegen, dar√ºber nachzudenken, wer sie denn eigentlich wirklich sind. Au√üerdem wollen wir beim Dreh mehr Erfahrung sammeln, uns Qualitativ im Vergleich zu Staffel 1 massivst steigern und die 'Jack'- Timeline meiner Geschichten beenden. 

Wenn alle einverstanden sind, w√ºrde ich nach M√∂glichkeit gerne im Winter mit dem Dreh weitermachen. Diesmal stehe ich auf jeden Fall, im Gegensatz zu bei Mafialiebe, komplett zu Story, Handlung und Co. Ich finde, diese Geschichte bietet einen bestm√∂glichen Abschluss f√ºr die Reihe 'Siegerlandchaos' und ich w√ºrde mich sehr freuen, wenn wir das dann zusammen und in besserer Qualit√§t hinkriegen üòä Da das Drehbuch auch um Einiges k√ºrzer und auf weniger Charakter- Konstellationen beschr√§nkt ist, gehe ich auch von einer schnelleren Umsetzungsm√∂glichkeit als bei Staffel 1: Mafialiebe aus. Drehtage w√ºrden diesmal nach M√∂glichkeit komplett danach ausgerichtet, wer an welchem Tag nach Absprache Zeit hat. 

Ver√∂ffentlicht soll die 2. Staffel mitsamt Bonusepisode ebenfalls auf YouTube werden. 

Gesuchte Rollen:

Luna Drews - Spielalter 20-30 (w/d) - 1 Drehtag - freundlich, f√ºrsorglich, zuh√∂rend, lebensfroh, ernst, heimlich schwanger, blonde Haare 

Bereits 12 Darsteller*innen + 2 Hunde sind Teil des Teams. Die Truppe scheint ganz lustig zu sein und einige Mitglieder kenne ich auch schon l√§nger.

Zus√§tzlich suchen wir einen neuen Drehort f√ºr Leas und Majas zu Hause. 

Ich suche keine Leute, die sagen: Ja, mach ich mal mit. Ich suche Leute, die sagen: Ja, das w√§re voll cool, dabei zu sein! 

Wenn Interesse besteht, meldet euch gerne bei mir :)
jappycreations@gmail.com 

Zu mir: Ich bin Sarah Marie Sch√§fer, geb. am 01.10.2003 in Siegen, und wohne aktuell in der N√§he von Siegen in einem kleinen Dorf. Nach dem ich meinem verstorbenen Hund Jack versprach, meine Pl√§ne in die Tat umzusetzen und gl√ºcklich zu werden, tat ich dies mit dem Beginn meines ersten Serienprojekts, das abgeschlossen wurde. Fortan spielte ich auch Theater und schloss einige andere Pl√§ne ab. In der Schauspielerei habe ich meinen Weg gefunden und m√∂chte diesen weitergehen. Trotz vieler H√ºrden, wie Autismus, Transidentit√§t und einigen gesundheitlichen Problemen gebe ich nicht so schnell auf und bleibe an meinen Pl√§nen dran.

Anbei sind ein paar Szenen aus Staffel 1 Folge 8 als Vorgeschmack :)

Halloüëãüèª Wir suchen f√ºr unser neues No- Budget- Serien- Projekt noch EINE hobbym√§√üige SCHAUSPIELERIN (w/d) f√ºr unser neues Projekt! Es wird sp√§ter noch ein Buch zur Staffel geben.

Titel: Siegerlandchaos Staffel 2: Traumawut + Abschlussepisode: Untergangseuphorie 

Genre: Krimi mit Fantasy- Elementen, Drama 

Logline:
Der Fokus liegt auf Lea, welche lernen muss, mit ihrem Trauma umzugehen, und dabei sowohl eine zerst√∂rerische als auch vers√∂hnliche Seite an sich entdeckt. Au√üerdem stellen sich die Fragen, was in Zukunft aus Sherlock Wickels Detektei werden soll und wer ein echtes oder ein falsches Spiel spielt. 

Zusammenfassung
Ausgangspunkt: Bei einem tragischen Ereignis verliert Lea ihre Ehefrau Maja, sowie so ziemlich alles, was ihr etwas bedeutet. Es stellen sich die Fragen, ob Maja noch lebt oder nicht, und wo der Verantwortliche f√ºr das Drama steckt. Lea gelangt langsam aber sicher an ihr Limit, w√§hrend Sherlock Wickel sie im Stich zu lassen scheint. 

Konflikt: Es gibt mehrere Konflikte. Eine Psychiatrie sollte Ben Saalfeld heilen, aber verdarb ihn, Aufgrund der Umst√§nde. Rache m√∂chte er an Sherlock Wickel, Markus Wattson und insbesondere Lea nehmen. Hilfe bekommt er dabei von Sarahs Erzfeind Ludwig, beruhend auf Gegenseitigkeit. Ludwig m√∂chte mit Jacks Kette, Sarah und Maja einen moralisch zwiesp√§ltigen Plan umsetzen, um sich selbst von Auswirkungen seiner Schuld zu befreien. Gleichzeitig geht es innerhalb seiner Organisation ebenfalls nicht mit rechten Dingen zu. 

Aufl√∂sung: Am Ende erh√§lt Lea wichtige Erkenntnisse √ºber 's sich selbst Verzeihen. Die Organisation wird √ºberf√ºhrt und die Detektei geschlossen. Es gibt Vers√∂hnungen, Happy Ends und Drama. Maja, Emmas bzw. Jillians Eltern, Ludwig, Liora und Ben werden sterben. Sherlock Wickel und Lea lernen, das Gl√ºck in kleinen Momenten zu sehen. 

Stimmung: Intensiv, d√ºster, humorvoll, spannend, mysteri√∂s, actiongeladen, nah an realen Erfahrungen mit Traumata 

Besonders geeignet f√ºr Menschen, die sich tiefer mit Gef√ºhlen auseinandersetzen m√∂chten. 

Das Drehbuch enth√§lt 125 Seiten, wovon bereits 11 gedreht wurden. Gedreht wird vermutlich wie gewohnt in Plittershagen (Freudenberg, NRW, nahe Siegen) und einem noch unbekannten Drehort als Leas zu Hause. Es sind ggf. Hunde vor Ort, weshalb Tierliebhaber erw√ºnscht sind :) Fahrtkosten k√∂nnen leider nicht √ºbernommen werden, aber f√ºr Spa√ü, Speis und Trank ist nat√ºrlich gesorgtüòä

Ziel des Projekts: Wir m√∂chten mit einer packenden Geschichte die Leute dazu bewegen, dar√ºber nachzudenken, wer sie denn eigentlich wirklich sind. Au√üerdem wollen wir beim Dreh mehr Erfahrung sammeln, uns Qualitativ im Vergleich zu Staffel 1 massivst steigern und die 'Jack'- Timeline meiner Geschichten beenden. 

Wenn alle einverstanden sind, w√ºrde ich nach M√∂glichkeit gerne im Winter mit dem Dreh weitermachen. Diesmal stehe ich auf jeden Fall, im Gegensatz zu bei Mafialiebe, komplett zu Story, Handlung und Co. Ich finde, diese Geschichte bietet einen bestm√∂glichen Abschluss f√ºr die Reihe 'Siegerlandchaos' und ich w√ºrde mich sehr freuen, wenn wir das dann zusammen und in besserer Qualit√§t hinkriegen üòä Da das Drehbuch auch um Einiges k√ºrzer und auf weniger Charakter- Konstellationen beschr√§nkt ist, gehe ich auch von einer schnelleren Umsetzungsm√∂glichkeit als bei Staffel 1: Mafialiebe aus. Drehtage w√ºrden diesmal nach M√∂glichkeit komplett danach ausgerichtet, wer an welchem Tag nach Absprache Zeit hat. 

Ver√∂ffentlicht soll die 2. Staffel mitsamt Bonusepisode ebenfalls auf YouTube werden. 

Gesuchte Rollen:

Luna Drews - Spielalter 20-30 (w/d) - 1 Drehtag - freundlich, f√ºrsorglich, zuh√∂rend, lebensfroh, ernst, heimlich schwanger, blonde Haare 

Bereits 12 Darsteller*innen + 2 Hunde sind Teil des Teams. Die Truppe scheint ganz lustig zu sein und einige Mitglieder kenne ich auch schon l√§nger.

Zus√§tzlich suchen wir einen neuen Drehort f√ºr Leas und Majas zu Hause. 

Ich suche keine Leute, die sagen: Ja, mach ich mal mit. Ich suche Leute, die sagen: Ja, das w√§re voll cool, dabei zu sein! 

Wenn Interesse besteht, meldet euch gerne bei mir :)
jappycreations@gmail.com 

Zu mir: Ich bin Sarah Marie Sch√§fer, geb. am 01.10.2003 in Siegen, und wohne aktuell in der N√§he von Siegen in einem kleinen Dorf. Nach dem ich meinem verstorbenen Hund Jack versprach, meine Pl√§ne in die Tat umzusetzen und gl√ºcklich zu werden, tat ich dies mit dem Beginn meines ersten Serienprojekts, das abgeschlossen wurde. Fortan spielte ich auch Theater und schloss einige andere Pl√§ne ab. In der Schauspielerei habe ich meinen Weg gefunden und m√∂chte diesen weitergehen. Trotz vieler H√ºrden, wie Autismus, Transidentit√§t und einigen gesundheitlichen Problemen gebe ich nicht so schnell auf und bleibe an meinen Pl√§nen dran.

Anbei sind ein paar Szenen aus Staffel 1 Folge 8 als Vorgeschmack :)

items.text:
# **CASTING CALL** (english version below)

Hey, wir suchen Schauspieler*innen f√ºr unseren Low-Budget-Studenten-Kurzfilm. Bei Interesse kontaktiert uns bitte per E-Mail: **[LivShortfilm2026@gmail.com](mailto:LivShortfilm2026@gmail.com)**.

Der Film wird an verschiedenen Locations gedreht, daher solltet ihr √ºber einen l√§ngeren Zeitraum (**mindestens eine Woche am St√ºck**) verf√ºgbar sein. 

**Unterk√ºnfte, Anfahrt und Verpflegung werden gestellt.**

** **

** **
## **Gesucht wird:**

**weiblich gelesene Person (S√§nger*in / Schauspieler*in)**

20-35 Jahre alt

**Voraussetzungen:**
* Musikalischer Hintergrund erforderlich (Sie sollten Gesangserfahrung und wenn m√∂glich Erfahrung mit dem Klavier haben) 
* Autof√ºhrerschein
* Deutsche Sprache C1

 

**M√§nnlich gelesene Person (Schauspieler*in)**

20-35 Jahre alt

**Voraussetzungen:**
* Autof√ºhrerschein
* Deutsche Sprache C1

 

**Drehtage:**

Anfang bis Mitte Januar

 

**Handlung:**

Die S√§ngerin Liv k√§mpft mit ihrer stagnierenden Karriere. Nachdem sie vor einem ihrer Auftritte zusammengebrochen ist, nimmt sie sich eine Auszeit mit ihrem Freund.

W√§hrend er glaubt, ihren Traum zu retten, versucht sie, sich von dem zu befreien, was aus diesem Traum geworden ist.

 

 

## **ENGLISH VERSION**

Hey, we are looking for actors for our low-budget student short film. If you are interested, please contact us by email: **LivShortfilm2026@gmail.com**.

The film will be shot at various locations, so you should be available for an extended period of time (at least one week at a time). 

**Accommodation, travel, and meals will be provided.**

 

 
## **We are looking for:**

**Actress/ Singer**

Aged 20-35

**Requirements:**
* Musical background required (you should have singing experience and, if possible, experience with the piano) 
* Driver's license
* German language C1

 

**Actor**

Aged 20-35

**Requirements:**
* Driver's license
* German language C1

 

**Shooting days:**

Early to mid-January

 

**Plot:**

Singer Liv is struggling with her stagnating career. After collapsing before one of her performances, she takes some time off with her boyfriend.

While he believes he is saving her dream, she is trying to free herself from what has become of that dream.

items.text:
Personal Short Film Project

SEEKING 2 ACTRESSES FOR MAIN CAST

WHEN: Dec 20‚Äì23, 2025

PAID: CAD $150 / Day

Project Title:

The Thought Experiment ‚ÄúMETA MONTAGE‚Äù

Genre:

Meta-psychological Drama / Experimental Metafiction / Postmodern Romance

Logline:

When a screenwriter finds himself inside the very film he‚Äôs writing, reality and fiction intertwine ‚Äî forcing him, his characters, and even the audience to confront the question: Who is truly creating whom?

A visual and interactive interpretation of the Multiverse Theory.

Production Details:

Dates: December 20‚Äì23, 2025

Location: Vancouver, BC

Rate: CAD $150 / day

Type: Independent Short Film (non-union, paid)

Casting:

JUDY (20s‚Äì30s)

As Character, Actor, and Generative AI.

A multi-layered role that shifts between human emotion and digital consciousness.

SOFIA (20s‚Äì30s)

Jack‚Äôs girlfriend ‚Äî the emotional axis between love, illusion, and authorship.

Updated on Oct 30 ‚Äì Clarification and Correction

I‚Äôd like to make a few corrections to my previous post.

On Oct 28th, I mentioned in the Casting Notice that this project is a ‚ÄúPersonal Student Short Film.‚Äù

However, I would like to clarify that this film is actually an independent personal project, not affiliated with the school.

Since I am currently studying at Vancouver Film School (VFS), I described it that way to indicate that it‚Äôs an independent short film made by a student,

but I realize this wording may have caused some misunderstanding.

I sincerely apologize for any confusion.

To be clear, this project is not a school-led production.

If you‚Äôre still interested, I‚Äôd be truly grateful for your audition.

I‚Äôll be sending those who emailed me a 6-minute short film I recently shot, along with a script excerpt from the project.

I‚Äôd really appreciate it if you could send me a video of yourself reading the script by November 9.

Contact:

Director / Writer / Producer : Yuri Kakuya

üìß hkjfilm@gmail.com

Hi folks! Looking for subjects to participate in a social experiment for CBC's Marketplace.

Unpaid/Volunteer but costs covered.

We're looking for people and families who have food affordability at the top of their mind to participate in an on-camera food challenge. 

Shooting dates throughout November...flexible & remote.

Please email jenny.cowley@cbc.ca if you're interested, and include where you're located, a bit about you and/or your family, why food affordability is at the top of your mind, and steps you've taken to save money on food costs.

items.text:
HOLDING PATTERN: A film noir by Nico Guin from Denver School of the Arts‚Äô VCA department!
Looking for 3 actors for a 5-minute film-noir!When a wealthy business woman meets a new love interest, she puts him to the test through a private investigator to find out if he can be trusted. 
Roles are not paid or promised.

ESTELLE - The younger wealthy business woman who is in love with John. She wants to test his potential as a love interest, but things take a turn. Estelle is cold, harsh, and confident, while also being sympathetic and unsettling.
JOHN -  John, a younger man who spends whatever money he has at the bar, who has been dating Estelle for a few months and really likes her. Unfortunately, when presented by Victor with the option to steal her fortune in the form of stocks and bonds, he decides the money is too enticing to decline, leading to his ultimate demise. 
VICTOR - The mysterious private investigator hired by Estelle to test whether or not John can be trusted as her future partner. He is ambiguous yet seemingly trustworthy to John, and offers him the job to steal Estelle‚Äôs assets.

We will be shooting during the first 3 weekends of November, and are pretty flexible with time of day! 
If you are interested or have any questions, you can reach out to me at 914900@dpsk12.net or 720-255-2717. Thank you!

items.text:
Casting call!

We're so excited to be casting for our female-focused feature film, Before Us!

Log line: Five strangers wrestle with motherhood and identity while, unbeknownst to them, their great grandmothers meddle from the afterlife. As their stories increasingly intertwine, the women must discover purpose from within themselves and from one another.

Genre: Dramedy

Paid, non-union

This first casting call includes our leads and key supporting roles, each paying $500-$750 depending on the success of fundraising and the final shooting schedule. We plan to shoot a teaser trailer and some social media content for fundraising purposes in November, with principal photography in January-February 2026. You can see full character breakdowns and audition submission instructions here: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1mi16s2oN0Gdn0KYzpTw6VKL1LIG1mytkHOXYFYM_a3M/edit?pli=1

We're casting for:

Izzy: 30, female, Chamorro (While a Chamorro actress is ideal, Izzy can be played by any Pacific Islander)

Agnes: 51, female, Chinese-American (While a Chinese actress is ideal, Agnes can be played by any actor of East Asian descent)

Sasha: 36, female, Black

Beatrice: Any age 50 or older, female, Black

Leticia: Any age 50 or older, female, Latina

Mabel: Any age 50 or older, female, Chinese (While a Chinese actress is ideal, she can be played by any actor of East Asian descent)

Man√•mko‚Äô: Any age 50 or older, female, Chamorro (While a Chamorro actress is ideal, she can be played by any Pacific Islander)

Margaret: Any age 50 or older, female, white

Foster: 29, male, any ethnicity

Please submit your audition via the form linked above by 11:59 pm on Saturday, November 1.

items.text:
Hello, 
We are looking for two performers to act in a short movie. ‚ÄúWhere the Light Shines‚Äù explores denial, anxiety, and female identity in a male-dominated society. The film reflects the tension between masculine and feminine energy ‚Äì control and surrender ‚Äì and how these forces collide in the face of inner truth.
The story uses contemporary movement and dance to showcase the troubled inner-word of the characters. You will be working closely with the director and choreographer to shape the narrative.
Females, non-binary and all ethnicities is encouraged to apply!<3 This is a third year Bachelor project.  
If you are ready to move with the lights, contact us at: edsh.production@gmail.com.

items.text:
Hey there! üëãüèªüòÉ

I‚Äôm Freya Tingley ‚Äî an Australian actress born and raised in Perth. I started acting at 14, taking weekly classes with a dream of one day building a career in Hollywood.

Bit by bit, I booked short films, found a local agent, and put together a demo reel ‚Äî all steps that helped me make the leap to LA just before turning 18. Not long after, I landed my first major role as a series regular on Netflix‚Äôs Hemlock Grove, followed by Once Upon a Time, Jersey Boys, and DOTA: Dragon‚Äôs Blood.

Of course, it wasn‚Äôt all smooth sailing and the journey had its pitfalls and huge learning curves along the way. But those ups and the downs gave me something valuable; an understanding of what works, what doesn‚Äôt and the exact steps to take to keep moving forward. 

Most acting schools don‚Äôt teach how to build a career ‚Äî they‚Äôll say ‚Äúget an agent,‚Äù or ‚Äúnetwork: it‚Äôs all about who you know!‚Äù - but there‚Äôs never a clear road map, or step-by-step plan to help you to make progress, no matter where you‚Äôre at that.

I‚Äôm growing a community for actors who want a clear game plan, strategy, and support to level up and turn their goals into reality.

Come hang out with us! I‚Äôd love to meet you, hear your story, and help you move closer to your dreams.

üëâ Join The Business of Acting www.skool.com/the-business-of-acting-9301/about?ref=387a46092b6b412b82c1a78a4c1a240e

See you there! üòÉ
‚Äî Freya

sharedPost.text:
üåÄüåÄüé•üèÜHighly advanced acting course on.line

---

üé¨ Unlock the Mind, Unlock the Scene

Ever wondered why some performances hit you right in the gut, while others just float by? It‚Äôs not luck ‚Äî it‚Äôs psychology, philosophy, and instinct.

In my course, we go deep into the human mind:

Freud ‚Üí Understand the hidden drives, inner conflicts, and desires that shape your character.

Jung ‚Üí Explore archetypes, shadows, and the collective patterns that give your role mythic resonance.

Nietzsche ‚Üí Learn to embrace struggle, chaos, and life itself, transforming it into raw energy for your performance.

This isn‚Äôt abstract theory ‚Äî it‚Äôs practical, on-set knowledge:

Build characters that feel alive, complex, and unforgettable.

Hit the emotional beats instinctively.

Turn tension, darkness, and chaos into performance gold.

Whether you‚Äôre in front of the camera or behind it, these tools take your craft to another level.

üí• Your mind is your stage ‚Äî let‚Äôs train it to perform.
LONG VERSION üåÄ1 to 1 on ZOOM,intensive,acting workshop.helping to push your emotions to the edge.leading to a powerful "sizzle"reel and possible employment on the 8 features I am shooting this year and next..long version.

Including "river talks"produced by "little pig films"

üåÄüé¨üé•üåö Exclusive 1-on-1 Acting Workshop

üî• Limited-Time Offer ‚Äì Only a Few Spots Left! üî•
(üì© Message Now to Secure Yours!)

"Imagine walking into an audition with unshakable confidence, delivering a performance so raw and real that the director can't look away."

This isn‚Äôt just another acting class. It‚Äôs an intensive experience designed to break barriers and elevate your craft.

---

üé≠ What Makes This Course Different?

"This course integrates the poetic realism of Tarkovsky, the practical wisdom of Michael Caine, and the transformative techniques of Stanislavski and Method Acting. Designed to deepen your craft, it focuses on authentic emotional connection and powerful storytelling."

Along with working with, Freud, Yung,and Nietzsche..to understand "subtext and archetypes".

üé¨ Created by a British Cinematographer/Director with 31 Years of Experience and 32 Features to His Name

üåç International Experience: Having worked on films worldwide, collaborating with actors and directors, I bring real-world insights from both sides of the camera. This course is designed to give actors a deep understanding of their craft, emphasizing emotional depth and character development.

üìΩ IMDb: www.imdb.com/name/nm1806508

üìΩ Showreel: https://enkiproductions1.8b.io

---

üé¨ Exclusive Opportunity ‚Äì A Direct Path to Real Work!

At the end of the course, each student will create a high-impact ‚Äúsizzle reel‚Äù, showcasing their strongest performance moments.

üîπ This reel will be personally passed on to the directors of the next 7 feature films I am working on as cinematographer.

üîπ That means real exposure‚Äîreal opportunities‚Äîreal chances for work.

üé≠ "This isn‚Äôt just training. This is your shot to be seen by directors actively casting for upcoming projects."

---

ü§î What You Will Learn:

üåÄ Emotional Range ‚Äì Master a full spectrum of emotions for believable, compelling performances.

üåÄ Character Development ‚Äì Create rich, multidimensional characters with depth and 
realism.

üåÄ Method Acting ‚Äì Use personal experiences to deliver raw, authentic performances.

üåÄ Working with Directors & Crew ‚Äì Learn how to hit marks, understand shooting ratios, and collaborate effectively.

üåÄ Scene Preparation ‚Äì Techniques for script interpretation, emotional connection, and performing under pressure.

üåÄ Industry Standards ‚Äì Create a professional showreel and understand how to stand out to casting directors.

---

üé¨ These Courses Are One-on-One with the Mentor/Director, Who Will Push You to Make the Performance Believable.

---

üé¨ Course Breakdown

Day 1: Moment-to-Moment Acting (Stanislavski‚Äôs Approach)

üîπ Breaking a Scene Down: Internal visualization and meditation to "become" the character.

üîπ Character Exercise: The Hitman‚Äôs First Kill

üìç Scene: A low-rent hotel room in Manhattan, lit by a dull winter‚Äôs midday light. The sad hum of a ceiling fan, distant sirens, muted traffic below. On the bed‚Äîa brand-new sniper rifle.(You will be encouraged to "visualize"this)

üí• "Actors I've trained have gone on to land real roles‚Äîthis course gives you what drama schools miss."

üîπ Exercise 1: Enter the room, pick up the gun, examine it, and prepare for the target.

üîπ Exercise 2: Explore multiple emotional shifts (relief, doubt, fascination, decision).

üåÄYou have entered the room you are safe (singular emotion)

üåÄYou see the gun on the bed,the awareness of your reality sinks in.

üåÄYou make a descion to approach the gun 

üåÄYou pick up the gun,initially you are captivated by the mastery of it,s creation (momentarily distracting you from the reality of what you are about to do.)

üåÄYou make the descion to kill(remember in this excercise this is a 1st time "hit person"..why do you make that descion?(Covered in class).

üåÄYou move to the window,practical ,Now you have decided action will take place.

Explore why using stanislavski techniques,of breaking a scene into ,moment by moment.

It is more fascinating to watch.on screen,the audience does not know "what is going on in your head"..but it is fascinated to watch,and it captures your audience.

üîπ Discussion: How do actors like Heath Ledger, Daniel Day-Lewis, and Dustin Hoffman make their characters so real? Insights from my own experiences on set.

üåÄ:(monologue)an actor,s ability to memorize lines is important .

üé¨:in the style of "the late great heath ledger of "Batman dark knights"(a crazed man sits with a portable nuclear bomb,on his lap):

üåÄ"So you imagine chaos was created in a day?(Sinister,sarcastic)(Pause/breath)"do you think e equals m squared (slow word by word,as if talking to a child),means we can travel back in time?(Smiles,and cricks his/her neck),no it just means we can build an atom bomb!!,and blow things up!(Smiles and claps hands gleefully),we are all going to die (bows as if on stage),and just by chance we,ll remember why.(Pause)...we even did this?,looks at camera slowly . reflectivity,or just perhaps...mmm I don,t know "nobody cares"!!!!!!.

Lifts button to camera and presses it!!!!..

Boom!!!(Note my last student took the entire session to make this believable).

End scene.üé¨üé¨

---

Day 2: Making Your Character Believable

üîπ Understanding the Psyche: Whether playing a killer or an ordinary person, you must know your character‚Äôs mind.research I had a director friend who contacted "Liam neelson"to understand him
Heath ledger locked himself in a hotel room
The actor from the "machinenist"almost starved himself to death.

üîπ Character Exercise: The Breaking Point

üìç Scene: A crowded supermarket. A tired voice announces deals over the PA. You feel unseen, unheard, frustrated‚Äîuntil suddenly, you‚Äôre holding an AK-47. (Scenes can be altered if a student is uncomfortable.)you open fire!!!.

Bang bang bang.
The feeling of power and saying 
F......you all.

Is almost zen like just firing the gun,every round as it falls to the ground is an expression of the rage of anger you feel about ,been born, having to survive,having to make a living,for this day and this day only!(You know for sure the police will kill you)

But this is your day!!!

I will direct you for this scene.

To make it believable

You will have to use "method"and the ability to "source"that"inner rage(which we all have).
To make the scene believable.

Shown to directors I know ..I imagine (if done right,they will be "blown away")

üîπ Alternative Scene: A Joker-like monologue before detonation.

I have script from this scene we can work with.
But it explores "chaos/anarchist"concepts (as expressed by the joker (heath ledger )In "Batman dark knights"

üîπ Alternative Scene: A video call to the person you love most‚Äîdesperately trying to convince them not to leave.

The point of this scene (if you choose it)is to make your performance totally believable.

üé≠ "Imagine the tension of a final phone call‚Äîthe stakes couldn‚Äôt be higher. This is where real acting happens."

üîπ Accents: British, American (Deep South), and Northern Irish accents for performance versatility.

üîπ Final Exercise: The Power of Stillness ‚Äì convey pure serenity in front of the camera.

The American Indians used to say "a camera steal,s your soul"

A film camera can almost "see inside you"
The purpose of this course is to help you create that "believability"and emotion.

---

Day 3: Working with a Director and Crew

üîπ Understanding your role in the filmmaking process.

üîπ Technical skills: hitting marks, lighting awareness, and camera shooting ratios.
If you don,t appreciate what your crew does,and are say arrogant,well does not make for a nice shoot?

Most actor,s I have worked with are empathetic,kind and understanding 
üîπ Collaborating with crew‚Äîcontinuity, sound, makeup, cinematography, and direction.

üìΩ Final Showreel Scenes:

üé≠ Sinister: "So you really think you got away with it?" You imagine that your karma was not noted,your actions had no consequences.

üé≠ Heartbroken: "But I didn‚Äôt mean it... please, don‚Äôt leave me‚Ä¶I know now that without you I could never imagine how my life would be"

üé≠ Insane (Joker-like): "Mmm... if E = mc¬≤, then time versus chaos... Means excistance is just a theory ,I have this bomb..the one thing Einstein /Oppenheimer manager to create..so bye bye..let,s push the button!!

üé≠ Flat & Emotionless: "We‚Äôre born, we live, we die. That‚Äôs it." If heaven exists,and we are re.born with "conciseness ",then heaven would become like hell,
As "time"and a sense of time ,knowing we are going one day ,gives us ..in way (deep pause look to camera)a security.

---

Day 4: Fear and Survival ‚Äì Personal Experience & Character Creation

üîπ Deep Dive: Exploring fear, survival, and desperation in character work.

üîπ Exercise 1: The Jungle Escape
üìç Scene: You‚Äôre lost in the jungle at night. Every step is agony, but stopping means death. You call out‚Äîpleading for help. No answer.

üé≠ Emotions to Explore:

1. Fear of death ‚Äì the realization that no one is coming.

2. Desperation ‚Äì the raw instinct to survive.

3. Physical exhaustion ‚Äì feeling your body give in.

üîπ Exercise 2: The Final Phone Call Redux
üìç Scene: You‚Äôre on the phone with a loved one. You need their help. If they refuse, it‚Äôs over.

üé≠ "This isn‚Äôt just acting‚Äîit‚Äôs about reaching deep into your own experiences to find truth in the performance."

------

üé¨:Session 5: Unlocking the Inner World ‚Äî Freud, Jung, and Nietzsche in Action

 üö®A short script will be given:

üé•:."Sometimes I just can,t feel my self inside,it,s as if something is missing ,but ..I can,t quite put my finger on it"

Jung ,Freud and Nietzsche will be discussed in class...there different philosophies on life .

Perform the script 3 times with those different subtexts in mind.

---

Objective:

To integrate the psychological and philosophical concepts we've explored (Freud's hidden desires, Jung's archetypes, and Nietzsche's self-empowerment) into a character's internal journey, enhancing the depth of performance and pushing actors toward more complex, dynamic roles.

---

üö®1. Understanding the Inner Conflict (Freud)

Exercise:
Guide your actors to explore a hidden desire or repressed emotion within their character that contradicts their outward behavior.
Example: An actor playing a ‚Äústoic‚Äù hero could uncover a deep fear of abandonment they are trying to repress, which sneaks through in moments of weakness.(Script will be given)

üåÄGoal:
Reveal the complexity of a character by exploring subconscious drives and how they create inner conflict in their actions.

---

üö®2. Finding the Archetypes (Jung)

üåÄExercise:
Ask your actors to identify which archetype (Hero, Shadow, Wise Old Man, Rebel, etc.) their character is embodying in the scene.
Then, have them break the archetype ‚Äî let them experiment with how the character could act outside their usual role to reveal something deeper about their personal growth.(Script will be given)

üåÄGoal:
Explore how different archetypes influence a character‚Äôs actions and how those archetypes evolve through the story.

---

üö®3. Creating the √úbermensch Moment (Nietzsche)

üåÄExercise:
Have your actors play out a moment where their character faces a crucible‚Äîa choice that pushes them beyond their old self and forces them to create their own values.
Example: A character might choose self-sacrifice to uphold their personal code, even though it risks everything (script will be given)

Goal:
Challenge the actor to play moments of personal transformation, where their character is creating their own power in the face of destruction or moral ambiguity.

---

üåÄ4. Integration and Performance

Exercise:
Give your actors a scene where all three elements come into play:

Freud's inner conflict (hidden desires or repressions)

Jung's archetypes (the character wearing multiple masks)

Nietzsche‚Äôs self-empowerment (the character breaking free and reimagining their world)
Guide them to play the scene with all these layers, digging into the internal battle, archetypal masks, and the potential for self-transformation.(Script will be given).

Goal:
Combine these psychological and philosophical elements to create a rich, multi-dimensional character.

---

Wrap-Up:

Discuss how each character‚Äôs internal journey was shaped by their hidden emotions, their spiritual archetypes, and their search for power.

Reflect on how they can continue to explore their characters‚Äô deeper layers in future roles.

üé¨ Final Performance (Day 4):

Students will perform a final emotional scene, bringing together everything they‚Äôve learned. These performances will be recorded as raw material for their showreel.

üí• Their best moments will be compiled into a high-impact sizzle reel‚Äîdirectly sent to directors casting for upcoming feature films.
That I am either producing or about to be cinematographer on.

---

üé¨üé• Ready to Elevate Your Acting?

üî• For Less Than the Price of a Casting Workshop, You Get 1-on-1 Coaching and a Real Chance for Work!

üì¢ LIMITED SPOTS AVAILABLE ‚Äì MESSAGE NOW TO SECURE YOUR PLACE!

üì© DM or Email: mikeenkiproductions1@gmail.com

Let‚Äôs create something unforgettable.
---

---

Mike Muschamp‚Äôs Philosophy Map ‚Äì The Big Five

1Ô∏è‚É£ Freud ‚Äì The Mind‚Äôs Hidden Drives

Core idea: Unconscious desires and fears shape behavior.

Use in acting/storytelling: Know why characters (and people) do what they do. Subtle gestures, hesitation, tension = meaningful.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Jung ‚Äì Archetypes & Shadows

Core idea: Universal patterns, archetypes, and the hidden ‚Äúshadow‚Äù influence life.

Use in acting/storytelling: Tap into archetypes to make characters mythic; explore shadow for emotional depth.

3Ô∏è‚É£ Nietzsche ‚Äì Will to Power & Self-Overcoming

Core idea: Life is chaos; create your own meaning and values.

Use in acting/storytelling: Turn struggle into strength, show transformation, act boldly.

4Ô∏è‚É£ Camus ‚Äì Absurdity & Joy in Struggle

Core idea: Life has no inherent meaning; joy comes from living fully despite it.

Use in acting/storytelling: Embrace absurdity in scenes, add existential tension and truth.

5Ô∏è‚É£ Viktor Frankl (‚ÄúFrank‚Äù) ‚Äì Meaning in Suffering

Core idea: Even in suffering, humans can find purpose; choosing your attitude = freedom.

Use in acting/storytelling: Transform hardship into performance, purpose, and inspiration.

---

How They Mix Together ‚Äì Your Signature Lens

Freud + Jung: Understand inner drives and archetypal patterns.

Nietzsche + Camus: Embrace chaos, self-overcome, find joy in struggle.

Frank: Give all of it purpose; turn learning and life into meaning.

Result: A philosophical toolkit that powers acting, directing, writing, and living

items.text:
‚ú® Ihr exklusives Shooting 2025 ‚Äì Erinnerungen, die bleiben ‚ú®
üì∏ Zwei Wunsch-Themen. Ein Profi-Team. Unvergessliche Bilder.

Ob f√ºr ihre Familie, ihren Partner, f√ºr sie selbst, ihr Business-Profil oder f√ºr eine Modelmappe:
Ein professionelles Shooting ist mehr als nur Fotos. Es ist ein Erlebnis, das man sp√ºrt‚Ä¶ und dann nat√ºrlich auch sieht!

Michael Diehl ist renommierter Fotograf aus Esslingen mit jahrzehntelanger Erfahrung in seinem stylischen Studio oder auf Location, mit dem Blick f√ºr das Besondere und der Gabe, jede Pers√∂nlichkeit zum Strahlen zu bringen.

Dinah Zahran ist BeautyCreator Visagistin mit Feingef√ºhl und Meisterhand. Sie hat das Auge f√ºrs Detail und ein Gesp√ºr daf√ºr, das Beste in ihnen hervorzuheben. Sie schminkt und stylt die Haare typgerecht und passend zum Outfit. Sie sorgt daf√ºr, dass sie sich wohl, sch√∂n und authentisch f√ºhlen.

Zusammen sind sie ein eingespieltes Team und schaffen eine Atmosph√§re, in der sie sich fallen lassen k√∂nnen: entspannt, herzlich und voller Energie.
Keine steifen Posen, kein k√ºnstliches L√§cheln, daf√ºr echte Momente und viel gute Laune.

üìÖ Termine ‚Äì limitierte Pl√§tze:
14.‚Äì16. November 2025 (Fr‚ÄìSo)
21.‚Äì23. November 2025 (Fr‚ÄìSo)
Slots: 10‚Äì12 Uhr | 13‚Äì15 Uhr | 16‚Äì18 Uhr
(Nur 18 Pl√§tze ‚Äì wenn weg, dann weg.)

üíÑ Das erwartet Sie:
- Typgerechtes Hair & Make-up (ca. 45 min) von Dinah
- 1-2 Stunden Shooting mit 2 Wunsch-Themen ihrer Wahl
- Hochaufl√∂sende Bilder ohne Wasserzeichen (Farbe, getont oder s/w)
- Professionelle Bearbeitung von je 1 Bild pro Thema nach Wahl
- Alle Nutzungsrechte f√ºr private & gesch√§ftliche Eigenpr√§sentation (Social Media, LinkedIn, Xing, Modelagenturen etc.)
- Das Styling mit entsprechender Mode sind ihre Lieblingsoutfits aus ihrem Kleiderschrank. Auf Wunsch helfen wir ihnen im Studio dann gerne bei der entsprechenden Zusammenstellung.

üéÅ Perfekt als Weihnachtsgeschenk:
F√ºr sie selbst, f√ºr ihren Lieblingsmenschen, f√ºr ihren Business-Headshot, ihre Fashion- oder Beauty-Portr√§ts, f√ºr ihr Modelbook oder einfach nur was sch√∂nes und sinnliches unterm Weihnachtsbaum ‚Äì alles ist m√∂glich.

Auch als Gutschein bis 23.12.25 verf√ºgbar.

üí∞ Preis:
Alles inklusive: 450 ‚Ç¨ zzgl. MwSt.

üì© Buchung:
Schreiben sie einfach eine PN oder WhatsApp, um ihren Wunschtermin zu sichern.
Studio-Preview: [https://lnkd.in/gtVy_vN7](https://lnkd.in/gtVy_vN7)
Mehr Eindr√ºcke: [www.mdiehl-photography.com](http://www.mdiehl-photography.com) & @[beautycreator.de](http://beautycreator.de)

‚ú® Lache, posiere, sei du selbst ‚Äì Michael und Dinah fangen die Momente ein, die bleiben.

Hello fellow Colorado actors. Many of you may not know that as a SAG member actors need to follow SAG rules. I have seen several violations of SAG rules, not only in our Denver market, but in New Mexico as well. Did you know that SAG rule 14 states:

A member cannot work as both a performer and a casting director, or a performer and a member of another theatrical teamster union, on the same production without the union's consent? 

Actors should not be casting directors due to a conflict of interest, as it can lead to biased decision-making in favor of their own acting career, and because the two roles require different skill sets. 

A casting director's job is to serve the production's needs by finding the best fit for a role, a process that requires a separate and objective perspective from the actor's self-interest in getting cast. 

If you know of anyone that is breaking SAG rule 14, I urge you to call or email SAG in Los Angeles and ask to speak with their violation‚Äôs department. You can also make the claim anonymously!Ôøº

SAG-AFTRA / (855) 724-2387
info@sagaftra.org

items.text:
Hey there! üëãüèªüòÉ

I‚Äôm Freya Tingley ‚Äî an Australian actress born and raised in Perth. I started acting at 14, taking weekly classes with a dream of one day building a career in Hollywood.

Bit by bit, I booked short films, found a local agent, and put together a demo reel ‚Äî all steps that helped me make the leap to LA just before turning 18. Not long after, I landed my first major role as a series regular on Netflix‚Äôs Hemlock Grove, followed by Once Upon a Time, Jersey Boys, and DOTA: Dragon‚Äôs Blood.

Of course, it wasn‚Äôt all smooth sailing and the journey had its pitfalls and huge learning curves along the way. But those ups and the downs gave me something valuable; an understanding of what works, what doesn‚Äôt and the exact steps to take to keep moving forward. 

Most acting schools don‚Äôt teach how to build a career ‚Äî they‚Äôll say ‚Äúget an agent,‚Äù or ‚Äúnetwork: it‚Äôs all about who you know!‚Äù - but there‚Äôs never a clear road map, or step-by-step plan to help you to make progress, no matter where you‚Äôre at that.

I‚Äôm growing a community for actors who want a clear game plan, strategy, and support to level up and turn their goals into reality.

Come hang out with us! I‚Äôd love to meet you, hear your story, and help you move closer to your dreams.

üëâ Join The Business of Acting www.skool.com/the-business-of-acting-9301/about?ref=387a46092b6b412b82c1a78a4c1a240e

See you there! üòÉ
‚Äî Freya

We're casting for our magical Tanfield Railway Christmas Experience in County Durham‚Äì and we‚Äôre on the lookout for charismatic, professional Christmas Elves to join the team!

üìç Location: Tanfield Railway Path, Newcastle upon Tyne NE16 5ET
üìÜ Contract: November ‚Äì December 2025
üí∏ Rate: ¬£14 per hour ‚Äî Pay & Half on Christmas Eve

‚ú® Requirements:

‚Ä¢ Entry-level acting skills

‚Ä¢ Immersive performance ability

‚Ä¢ Must absolutely love Christmas!

You‚Äôll be part of a heartwarming festive experience for families and children, working alongside our Santa and Train Conductor in a beautifully themed setting.

üßù‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è We‚Äôre looking for:

‚Ä¢ Confident, energetic performers with great improvisation skills

‚Ä¢ Friendly, reliable team players

‚Ä¢ Previous experience working with children or in character-based roles is a plus

üìå Important Info:

‚Ä¢ Costume and full training provided

‚Ä¢ Paid rehearsals and site visits will be scheduled in early November ‚Äì exact dates TBC

‚Ä¢ Below is the confirmed list of working dates, and shift times : 

‚úÖ Shift Dates & Times

‚Ä¢ Sat, Nov 29 - 10:45am - 6:45pm 

‚Ä¢ Sun, Nov 30 - 10:45am - 6:45pm 

‚Ä¢ Sat, Dec 6 - 10:45am - 6:45pm 

‚Ä¢ Sun, Dec 7 - 10:45am - 6:45pm 

‚Ä¢ Sat, Dec 13 - 10:45am - 6:45pm 

‚Ä¢ Sun, Dec 14 - 10:45am - 6:45pm 

‚Ä¢ Sat, Dec 20 - 10:45am - 6:45pm 

‚Ä¢ Sun, Dec 21 - 10:45am - 6:45pm 

‚Ä¢ Tue, Dec 23 - 10:45am - 6:45pm 

‚Ä¢ Wed, Dec 24 - 10:45am - 6:45pm (Christmas Eve ‚Äì Pay & a half) 

üì© To apply:
Send your CV, headshot, and any relevant performance footage to: castings@evokeents.com
Subject line: TANFIELD RAILWAY CHRISTMAS CONTRACT
Tell us a little about why you‚Äôd be a great fit & the dates you're interested in working ‚Äî we‚Äôd love to hear from you!

items.text:
I am helping a friend with her Comedy Drama short film and we are looking to cast a 70+ years old White Male to play ‚ÄòJim‚Äô

Jim sees his first girlfriend when coming home from a walk‚Ä¶ but‚Ä¶ she is still 21‚Ä¶

Thought it‚Äôs comical, he is still battling with his sense of reality.

The fee is ¬£100 for the day due to the low/no-budget.

Food and travel would be provided + the footage.

The shoot will be 1 day in the last 2 weeks of November in London, still TBC.

If you are interested, please email yanxancasting@gmail.com with ‚ÄòJim‚Äô as a subject.

If you already applied from the previous post you don‚Äôt need to reapply.

For the first time ever, actors everywhere can learn The Trinity Acting Method in full ‚Äî a groundbreaking system that simplifies acting into its most honest and achievable form.

I created the Trinity Acting Method to open the door for everyone ‚Äî to make great acting something anyone can understand, develop, and apply, whether you‚Äôre just starting out or already working in film and TV.

Now, I need your help to get this message out into the world. üôè
Please pre-order your copy today, and if you believe in what I do ‚Äî in making acting accessible, inclusive, and truly transformative ‚Äî please share this link on your socials.

We're casting for our magical Tanfield Railway Christmas Experience in County Durham‚Äì and we‚Äôre on the lookout for charismatic, professional Christmas Elves to join the team!

üìç Location: Tanfield Railway Path, Newcastle upon Tyne NE16 5ET
üìÜ Contract: November ‚Äì December 2025
üí∏ Rate: ¬£14 per hour ‚Äî Pay & Half on Christmas Eve

‚ú® Requirements:

‚Ä¢ Entry-level acting skills

‚Ä¢ Immersive performance ability

‚Ä¢ Must absolutely love Christmas!

You‚Äôll be part of a heartwarming festive experience for families and children, working alongside our Santa and Train Conductor in a beautifully themed setting.

üßù‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è We‚Äôre looking for:

‚Ä¢ Confident, energetic performers with great improvisation skills

‚Ä¢ Friendly, reliable team players

‚Ä¢ Previous experience working with children or in character-based roles is a plus

üìå Important Info:

‚Ä¢ Costume and full training provided

‚Ä¢ Paid rehearsals and site visits will be scheduled in early November ‚Äì exact dates TBC

‚Ä¢ Below is the confirmed list of working dates, and shift times : 

‚úÖ Shift Dates & Times

‚Ä¢ Sat, Nov 29 - 10:45am - 6:45pm 

‚Ä¢ Sun, Nov 30 - 10:45am - 6:45pm 

‚Ä¢ Sat, Dec 6 - 10:45am - 6:45pm 

‚Ä¢ Sun, Dec 7 - 10:45am - 6:45pm 

‚Ä¢ Sat, Dec 13 - 10:45am - 6:45pm 

‚Ä¢ Sun, Dec 14 - 10:45am - 6:45pm 

‚Ä¢ Sat, Dec 20 - 10:45am - 6:45pm 

‚Ä¢ Sun, Dec 21 - 10:45am - 6:45pm 

‚Ä¢ Tue, Dec 23 - 10:45am - 6:45pm 

‚Ä¢ Wed, Dec 24 - 10:45am - 6:45pm (Christmas Eve ‚Äì Pay & a half) 

üì© To apply:
Send your CV, headshot, and any relevant performance footage to: castings@evokeents.com
Subject line: TANFIELD RAILWAY CHRISTMAS CONTRACT
Tell us a little about why you‚Äôd be a great fit & the dates you're interested in working ‚Äî we‚Äôd love to hear from you!

**ACTORS WANTED - PAID**

We‚Äôre currently looking for an actor to play **Timmy**, a supporting role in our upcoming short film exploring themes of male loneliness and quiet connection.

Preferably actor will be based close to filming location (Surrey)
